# echo.scenario — proves record.Open + emission sites + the recorder
# replay buffer compose end-to-end, AND that @client/<name> option
# writes are safe against the attached-pump goroutine reading other
# options off the same table. new-session creates the session and emits
# pane.ready. client spawn opens a synthetic client whose server-side
# pump reads session-scope options (status, default-shell defaults
# walking up to serverOptions) while running its render loop. The
# scenario's own per-line connections then run wait + client kill, and
# kill writes @client/<name> on serverOptions — the same table the
# pump's parent-chain Gets are walking. Without internal/options taking
# a mutex, -race flags this as a data race; with the mutex, the
# scenario completes cleanly.
#
# Also exercises the pane.spawning emission site: the event fires
# before pty.Spawn so scenarios observe spawn intent even on failure.
# pane.exited is emitted from waitLoop too but does not fire reliably
# inside the 5s wait window after `client kill c` (the shell child
# does not always reap that quickly under -race), so it is not
# asserted here.

new-session
wait pane.spawning
client spawn c
wait pane.ready
client at c "echo hello\n"
client kill c
